    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA306-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu puṉamaṭi uraittuc ceṟippaṟivuṟīiyatu. 2. ciṟaippuṟamumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what informed of confinement by talking about the bending [crops] on the fields. 2. It is also [HIS] being behind the fence.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA306">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            tantai vittiya meṉṟiṉai paipayac</l>
<l>            ciṟukiḷi kaṭital piṟakkiyā vaṇatō</l>
<l>            kuḷirpaṭu kaiyaḷ koṭicci celkeṉa</l>
<l>            nalla viṉiya kūṟi mellak</l>
<l>            koyaṟuṭaṅ kiṉarē kāṉavar koṭuṅkuraṟ</l>
<l>            kulavuppoṟai yiṟutta koṟṟalai yiruvi</l>
<l>            viḻavoḻi viyaṉkaḷaṅ kaṭuppat teṟuvarap</l>
<l>            paita lorunilaik kāṇa vaikal</l>
<l>            yāṅku varuvatu kollō tīñcoṟ</l>
<l>            ceṟittōṭ ṭelvaḷaik kuṟumakaḷ</l>
<l>            ciṟupuṉat talkiya perumpuṟa nilaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Where [is] afterwards the chasing away of small parrots,</l>
<l>gently, from the soft millet sown by father?</l>
<l rend="indent">“The creeper woman, stirring the kettle-drum in her hand, may go,”</l>
<l rend="indent3">[thus] talking good [and] pleasing words, softly,</l>
<l>the foresters have begun to pluck [the corn].</l>
<l>How [will there be] coming at daytime,</l>
<l rend="indent">to see the one state of suffering, scorchingly(?),</l>
<l rend="indent2">like the wide ground left behind from a festival,</l>
<l rend="indent">of stubbles, with heads felled, brought down to a gleaming burden</l>
<l rend="indent">of bent ears,</l>
<l rend="indent">[to see]<note place="foot">How to construe the last two lines ending in <term xml:lang="ta">nilai</term>? Do we have to read a second, awkwardly positioned direct object to <term xml:lang="ta">kāṇa</term> in line 8? Is <term xml:lang="ta">nilai</term> supposed to be the subject of <term xml:lang="ta">varuvatu</term> (but then we would expect <term xml:lang="ta">āvatu</term>)? Do we have to construe circularly and take <term xml:lang="ta">nilai</term> as an unmarked locative: "Where [will be] the chasing away ..., in [her given] state ..."?</note> the state of the large back that abided in the small field</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the little woman with light bangles in a tight multitude,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with sweet words?</l>
      </lg>
      </div>
